<item>
            <title>[FLINK-1326] The output serializers may consume excessive memory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1326</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SpanningRecordSerializer creates large byte arrays to buffer records during serialization. Since they never release the records, they may occupy a large amount of memory. Currently, we use one per output partition, which is due to the original architecture.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are two ways to fix this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 1. Use only one serializer per output, rather than one per output partition. This is the preferable way in the long run anyways.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 2. Release the arrays in the serializer (quick fix).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
